gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bulls 124, Rockets 119
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bulls defeated the Rockets, 124-119, in OT. Coby White led the Bulls with 30 points, eight assists, and six 3PT as Zach LaVine (25 points, season-high 13 rebounds, seven assists) and Nikola Vucevic (18 points, 15 rebounds) totaled 43 points. Alperen Sengun scored 19 of 25 points in Q4 and OT, along with nine rebounds, and five assists as Fred VanVleet added 20 points and 10 assists for Houston. The Bulls have now won three games in a row and improve to 18-21 as the Rockets move to 18-18.
